What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you love yourself, take this class.

This was one of the most fun classes I've taken at Yale. I looked forward to going to class every time. Lectures were super interactive and there was a lively energy throughout the semester that made learning these concepts so fun. I would recommend this course to other students!

Very good course -- starting from level 0, worked through notes, scales, chords, harmony, rhythm/melody/form, etc. Also had a few days discussing non-Western music. Greater understanding of classical and pop music.
Extremely fun class! You learn a lot in a short period of time. Homework can get a bit tedious but the class is great.

A great intro course to music theory. Even if you have a basic understanding of music theory, this is still a good place to start in the Yale music program, as it is very comprehensive and really solidifies the knowledge before you move onto a higher level class.
Relaxed environment in which you learn intro music skills
A fun class but might require more work than you think
